cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.MM

This paper deals with predicting the popularity of online content, which involves analyzing user access and consumption patterns. This falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), which deals with the study of social networks and their impact on information dissemination. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to model the accrual of views and votes on content, which falls under Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the differences in how content is consumed on different portals, which relates to the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with predicting the long-term dynamics of individual submissions, which falls under the sub-category of Software Development (cs.SD).
